-- Ravens Fire Offensive Coordinator Cameron After Loss, ESPN Says
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-12-10T17:00:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-10/ravens-fire-offensive-coordinator-cameron-after-loss-espn-says.html
The Baltimore Ravens fired offensive
coordinator Cam Cameron and replaced him with quarterbacks coach
 Jim Caldwell , ESPN reported, citing a person familiar with the
situation.  Cameron, 51, was in his fifth season with Baltimore. The
Ravens are first in the American Football Conference North
Division with 9 wins and 4 losses. The club has lost two
consecutive regular season games for the first time since 2009.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  